item.title: Macro Backdrop Doesn't Justify EUR/USD Below 1.05, Says MUFG
item.description: A macro backdrop of recession doesn’t mean EUR/USD is heading lower, MUFG said, adding that “a level of 1.0500 for EUR/USD in large part we believe captures the current divergence between the euro-zone and the U.S.”

item.title: Oil Continues Slide as Investors Eye Middle East Conflict
item.description: Oil prices continued to drop, amid worries that the wider Middle Eastern region could become embroiled in the current conflict in Israel.

item.title: Hurricane Otis Churns Into Mexico's Acapulco as Category 5 Storm
item.description: Otis made landfall on Mexico’s Pacific Coast as authorities warned of torrential rain, landslides and flash flooding and urged people living near rivers or ravines to evacuate.

item.title: Bonds Are Volatile Now, But Offer Value in The Long Term
item.description: The environment for fixed income is a “great one” for long-term investors, despite the volatility in markets, PGIM Fixed Income said, adding that bond yields are a lot higher and cyclical headwinds suggest value over the medium term.

item.title: Heineken's 3Q Clears the Way for 2024 Prospects
item.description: Heineken’s 3Q performance was slightly weak, but the backed guidance and the likely absence of any major changes to consensus estimates should support share increases, Citi said.

item.title: Deutsche Bank Anticipates Accelerated Shareholder Returns
item.description: Deutsche Bank said it anticipated being able to accelerate and expand shareholder returns to 2025 and beyond after third-quarter revenue rose 3% but net profit fell on rising costs and taxes.

item.title: Heineken Backs Views Despite Seeing Weaker Demand
item.description: Heineken reported a third-quarter revenue of €8 billion, missing consensus forecast, but backed its 2023 guidance of stable to mid-single digit organic growth in operating profit.

item.title: Dassault Systemes Boosts EPS Forecast
item.description: Dassault Systemes confirmed its full-year guidance and raised its earnings-per-share outlook to a range between €1.19 and €1.21 following a rise in revenue and an operating margin that was slightly above expectations in the third quarter.

item.title: Lloyds Banking Backs 2023 Guidance on Higher Third-Quarter Pretax Profit
item.description: The British bank reported a pretax profit of 1.86 billion pounds in the third-quarter compared with a restated £576 million for the same period a year earlier.

item.title: Porsche Backs Full-Year Guidance
item.description: Porsche confirmed its 2023 outlook for operating return on sales after reporting a 13% revenue rise for the first nine months due to a strong performance in Europe, the U.S., and emerging markets.

item.title: Telenor Profit Beats Forecast on Nordics Growth
item.description: Telenor posted better-than-expected third-quarter profit and underlying earnings after seeing solid growth in the Nordics and synergies in Asia.

item.title: Beiersdorf Upgrades Sales Guidance on Strong Performance
item.description: Beiersdorf upgraded its sales guidance for the full year after recording a strong performance in the first nine months.

item.title: Santander Sees 2023 Targets on Track
item.description: Santander said it remained on track to meet its 2023 targets after it posted third-quarter earnings above forecast, with income from higher interest rates boosting its top line.

item.title: Hong Kong Plans Stamp Duty Cut to Boost Stock Market
item.description: Hong Kong will lower its stamp duty on stock transfers and reduce bourse market data fees to boost the competitiveness of one of Asia’s largest stock markets.

item.title: 'I'm Not OK,' Alaska Airlines Pilot Said Before Allegedly Trying to Disable Engines
item.description: Joseph David Emerson faces federal criminal charge of interfering with flight crew members, and court documents suggested psychedelic mushrooms may have played a role.

item.title: GOP Picks Mike Johnson as Speaker Nominee After Tom Emmer Stumbles
item.description: The Republican Party remains deeply divided three weeks since Kevin McCarthy was ousted as speaker.

item.title: Google's business grew faster than it has in more than a year, a signal that online advertising buyers are gaining confidence in the improving economic outlook.
item.description: Google’s business grew faster than it has in more than a year, a signal that online advertising buyers are gaining confidence in the improving economic outlook.

item.title: China removed its defense minister, the second time in three months that Chinese leader Xi abruptly axed a minister he had picked for his third-term government.

item.title: GM is abandoning a self-imposed target to build 400,000 electric vehicles by mid-2024, the latest sign that automakers are concerned about the viability of the market for battery-powered cars.
